claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: A table presenting vaccine effectiveness (VE) percentages (with 95% confidence intervals) for various influenza vaccines—recombinant quadrivalent influenza vaccine (RIV4), standard dose quadrivalent influenza vaccine (SD-IIV4), and RIV4 combined with high-dose IIV4 plus adjuvanted IIV (Adj-IV)—compared to no vaccination, stratified by age groups (18–64 years and ≥65 years) and by sex subgroups. does not support the claim because the table only shows comparative VE data and does not discuss production processes, mutations in cell- or egg-based vaccines, or their effect on vaccine effectiveness.
